Today was a good day, I completed my first 14er. It was no lie the hardest thing I have EVER done. I would be lying if I said some cliche like "you never know how strong you are..." Today was another lesson of total dependency on the Lord and relying on HIS strength. No way I could've done it on my own strength. I wanted to quit and cry numerous times but I kept reminding myself I was there to learn a lesson and I didn't want to miss it. I also got to enjoy beautiful scenery and mark something off my bucket list. Ended the night with the lunar eclipse. A day I'll never forget. #love #live #life #14er #grayspeak #grayspeaksummit #thelordisgood #lunareclipse #september #27 #14ft #bucketlist
